.TH term "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Terminal Command"
.SH NAME
term \- Launch a configured terminal with SMI profiles
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B term
.RI [ PROFILE_NAME... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B term
is a smart terminal launcher that integrates with SMI profiles.
It attempts to find and launch a suitable terminal emulator (xfce4-terminal, gnome-terminal, ptyxis, mate-terminal, konsole, or xterm) in the current working directory.
.PP
If a \fBDISPLAY\fR is available, it loads the specified \fIPROFILE_NAME\fR(s) and launches the GUI terminal.
If no \fBDISPLAY\fR is present, it falls back to \fBterm-activate\fR(1) to start a POSIX shell with the loaded profiles.
.SH PROFILES
Profiles are searched for in \fB~/.term/\fR and then in the system profiles directory. They are shell scripts with a \fB.profile\fR suffix.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Imre Tabur.
